column9: In my wellbeing services county, I should be able to get non-urgent treatment in primary health care within two weeks.
column10: Customer fees for public healthcare should be reduced.
column11: It is right that public money is spent to support people's use of private healthcare.
column12: One round-the-clock specialist hospital with emergency services will be enough in my wellbeing services county in the future.
column13: I am prepared to compromise on the social and health services of my home municipality if it is in the interest of the entire wellbeing services county.
column14: My wellbeing services county should attract doctors to health centers with financial incentives, even if that means cutting spending elsewhere.
column15: My wellbeing services county should attract care staff from abroad.
column16: My wellbeing services county must ensure that caregivers have a good command of Finnish or Swedish.
column17: My wellbeing services county should also offer undocumented people healthcare that is not required by law.
column18: This wellbeing services county should stop providing free contraception for young people.
column19: My wellbeing services county should train social and healthcare workers about the diversity of sexual orientation and gender.
column20: It is right that even small hospitals in Swedish-speaking areas be allowed maintain 24-hour special medical care services due to linguistic rights.
column21: Young people should be able to access mental health services without an appointment in my wellbeing services county.
column22: We should add more beds to 24-hour service housing for the elderly, even if it costs more.
column23: In eldercare, home visits can be replaced by remote services.
column24: Adult children should take more responsibility for caring for their elderly parents than they do now.
column25: We must accept that one's place of residence affects the availability of basic social and healthcare services.
column26: This wellbeing services county should reduce its purchase of child protection services from large companies.
column27: Drug users should have the opportunity to exchange dirty needles for clean ones in all the municipalities in my wellbeing services county.
column28: The current fire brigades must be maintained, even in remote areas.
column29: Wellbeing services counties should be given the right to collect tax.
column30: The number of wellbeing services counties should be reduced from the current 21.
column31: Well-being areas must make budget cuts within the required timeframe, even if that means that services must be quickly reduced.
column32: No-one should be allowed to hold triple roles as MP, municipal councillor and regional councillor at the same time.
column33: My wellbeing services county must take into account the reduction of climate emissions in all its decisions.
